<%= form_tag '/event_new', method: 'patch' do %>

<h2 id="heading_main">An advertisement with RubyJobs is free and is aimed purely at letting quality local developers know about your vacancy</h3><br>

<p id="text_headings">To keep the site amazing for both employers as well as developers we do have  advertising criteria to follow. Also note the best way to attract great talent isn't necessarily just advertising. Consider <a>creating a company bio</a> (highly recommended), you may want to <a>message the mailing list</a>, consider <a>browsing our actively looking for work developers </a> or see our tips on <a>Raising your companies brand awareness</a>.</p>

<p id="text_headings"><b>Thanks to  community input RubyJobs is 100% free and is riding Ruby On Rails</b></p>

<div class="col-md-12">
  <div class="thumbnail" id="icon_box">
    <i class="fa fa-camera-retro fa-4x" id="icon"></i>
    <div class="caption">
      <h3 id="heading_basic">Text Here</h3>
      <label>Job Title:</label><BR />
      <input class="std_input" name='job_title_input' autofocus required><BR />
      <label>Seniority:</label><BR />
      5 tick boxes go here
      <label>Location:</label><BR />
      <input class="std_input" name='location_input' ><BR />
      <label>Perks of the role:</label><BR />
      <textarea cols="50" rows="7" name='description_input'></textarea><BR />
      <label>Necessary Skills:</label><BR />
      <textarea cols="50" rows="7" name='skills_required'></textarea><BR />
      <label>How To Apply:</label><BR />
      <textarea cols="50" rows="7" name='apply_details'></textarea><BR />
      <button class="btn">Create</button>
      <div id="buttons_div">


      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<% end %>
